rest_of_day_open: Same old. I will just continue working my two jobs, and then going home. I will make sure to try to keep my family as safe as possible, by showering and not making contact with them until I am decontaminated. I will try to sleep a lot because it always feels like I lack sleep.
critical_positive: I think we are at different points in our lives, but she is still fun to talk to. She's in college with a similar degree as mine so we got to talk about it. We have similar views about current national events so we were able to keep the conversation going.
critical_negative: I think I talked too much, more than her. I got excited talking about my boyfriend so I think I dominated the conversation. I was thinking of that, but I couldn't stop talking. I feel bad, I wish I asked more questions about her, I think I sounded a tad bit self-centered.

rest_of_day_open: I see the rest of my week going okay. I'm visiting my boyfriend right now, which is definitely nice. After I return home, I'll probably be productive on cleaning my house and creative projects. Because of the pandemic, I think the rest of the week will be fairly monotonous but hopefully fulfilling.
critical_positive: My conversation partner and I compared experiences during the pandemic. This topic gave us something easy to talk about from which we could transition to other subjects. My partner talked about the way the pandemic affected her job, her relationship, and her family, which let me learn about her life in a natural way.
critical_negative: My partner talked a lot about herself and didn't ask many questions, which made it harder for me to share as well. For me, 25 minutes isn't long enough for me to really open up to someone, which resulted in my end of the conversation being mostly surface-level information.
